            <langmaterial id="ref19" label="Language of Materials note">Materials are in English</langmaterial>
            <abstract id="ref24" label="Abstract">The collection's interviews were conducted by Robin Kelley as research for his book 
                <title render="italic">Hammer and Hoe: Alabama Communists During the Great Depression.</title> The book, which was published by the University of North Carolina Press in 1990, documents the activities of the Alabama Communist Party in the 1930s and the impact of race and other cultural identities on the movement. The collection contains twelve oral history interviews taken by Kelley and one recorded radio program.</abstract>
            <origination label="creator">
                <persname rules="aacr" source="naf">Kelley, Robin D. G.</persname>
            </origination>
        </did>
        <acqinfo id="ref13">
            <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition note</head>
            <p>Collection was donated by Robin Kelley in 1997.</p>
        </acqinfo>
        <bioghist id="ref15">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>The collection's interviews were conducted by Robin Kelley as research for his book 
                <title render="italic">Hammer and Hoe: Alabama Communists During the Great Depression</title>. The book, which was published by the University of North Carolina Press in 1990, documents the activities of the Alabama Communist Party in the 1930s and the impact of race and other cultural identities on the movement.</p>
        </bioghist>
